## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 2.1: Create Basic Admin Dashboard Layout and Navigation**
  - [ ] Create admin route protection logic (extending middleware from Story 1.6)
  - [ ] Implement admin layout component (using MUI v6)
  - [ ] Build persistent left sidebar navigation (fixed width, always expanded on desktop/tablet)
  - [ ] Add ordered navigation links for all admin functions (following the specified order)
  - [ ] Create admin landing page with welcome message
  - [ ] Implement visual indication for currently active/selected admin section
  - [ ] Ensure responsive design (note: admin sidebar doesn't need to be collapsible on mobile for MVP)
  - Success criteria: Admin dashboard with secure routes and consistent navigation
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (Authentication, Middleware)

- [ ] **Story 2.2: Implement User Profile Management (Self-Service)**
  - [ ] Create dedicated profile page at `/settings/profile`
  - [ ] Add read-only user name display (disabled MUI TextField)
  - [ ] Implement password change section:
    - [ ] Add fields for current password (if set), new password, confirm password
    - [ ] Implement client-side validation (passwords match, validation based on admin app settings)
    - [ ] Add inline error messages
  - [ ] Create avatar management section:
    - [ ] Implement current avatar display or initials fallback
    - [ ] Add drag-and-drop upload and file select button (JPG/PNG/GIF, max 1MB)
    - [ ] Implement optional preview
    - [ ] Add "Remove Avatar" button with confirmation dialog
  - [ ] Implement avatar fallback logic:
    - [ ] Use 1st letter of username or 1st letter of first 2 words if space exists
    - [ ] Generate background color based on hash of username
  - [ ] Add Layout & Appearance Preferences section (from Story 4.1)
  - [ ] Build backend APIs for profile operations:
    - [ ] Password change endpoint with validation
    - [ ] Avatar upload endpoint with file handling
    - [ ] Avatar removal endpoint
  - [ ] Implement UI state management for async operations (loading, success, error)
  - [ ] Add success/error feedback via MUI Snackbar/Alert
  - Success criteria: Users can manage their profiles (password, avatar)
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 2.3: Implement Admin User Management**
  - [ ] Create user management page at `/admin/users`
  - [ ] Build user list display with all required columns:
    - [ ] Avatar (with fallback)
    - [ ] Login Name
    - [ ] Role
    - [ ] Status (Active/Disabled as MUI Chip)
    - [ ] Last Login (formatted)
    - [ ] Created At (formatted)
    - [ ] Actions column
  - [ ] Implement "Create New User" functionality:
    - [ ] Add prominent green MUI Button
    - [ ] Create dialog with form fields (name, role)
    - [ ] Implement client-side validation
    - [ ] Add confirmation dialog before submission
  - [ ] Add "Edit User" capability:
    - [ ] Create dialog with pre-filled fields
    - [ ] Add confirmation dialog before saving changes
  - [ ] Implement disabled "Delete User" button with tooltip
  - [ ] Add safeguards:
    - [ ] Prevent admin from changing own role if sole active admin
    - [ ] Prevent admin from disabling own account if sole active admin
  - [ ] Create backend APIs for user management:
    - [ ] GET endpoint to list all users
    - [ ] POST endpoint to create new user (with automatic UserSetting creation)
    - [ ] PUT endpoint to update user details
  - [ ] Integrate with user registration control setting (Story 2.5)
  - [ ] Implement UI refresh after operations
  - [ ] Add success/error feedback via MUI Snackbar
  - Success criteria: Admins can list, create, and edit users (name, role, status)
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1, Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 2.4: Implement Application Branding Management**
  - [ ] Define SystemSetting model fields for branding:
    - [ ] appName (String, default "ControlCenter")
    - [ ] logoPath (String, optional)
    - [ ] faviconPath (String, optional)
  - [ ] Create branding management page at `/admin/branding`
  - [ ] Add application name customization:
    - [ ] MUI TextField for app name
    - [ ] Save button with confirmation dialog
  - [ ] Implement logo image upload:
    - [ ] Create drag-and-drop zone and file select button
    - [ ] Add client-side validation (JPG/PNG/SVG, max 1MB)
    - [ ] Implement optional preview
    - [ ] Add "Remove Custom Logo" option with confirmation
  - [ ] Add favicon image upload:
    - [ ] Create drag-and-drop zone and file select button
    - [ ] Add client-side validation (ICO/PNG, defined dimensions)
    - [ ] Add "Remove Custom Favicon" option with confirmation
  - [ ] Build backend APIs for branding management:
    - [ ] GET endpoint to retrieve current branding settings
    - [ ] PUT endpoint to update branding settings
    - [ ] POST endpoints for file uploads
    - [ ] DELETE endpoints for removing custom files
  - [ ] Implement dynamic application of branding settings in UI
  - [ ] Create proper file storage strategy in `/public/branding/`
  - [ ] Add success/error feedback via MUI Snackbar
  - Success criteria: Admins can customize app name, logo, and favicon
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1

- [ ] **Story 2.5: Implement User Registration Control Setting**
  - [ ] Define SystemSetting model field:
    - [ ] allowAdminUserCreation (Boolean, default true)
  - [ ] Add section to admin settings page at `/admin/settings`
  - [ ] Create UI for toggling user creation permission:
    - [ ] MUI Switch for "Allow New User Creation by Admins"
    - [ ] Display current state
    - [ ] Add confirmation dialog before applying changes
  - [ ] Implement persistence mechanism using SystemSetting model
  - [ ] Update user creation UI based on setting:
    - [ ] Hide/disable "Create New User" button when disabled
    - [ ] Add backend validation to reject creation when disabled
  - [ ] Build backend API for settings management:
    - [ ] GET endpoint to retrieve current settings
    - [ ] PUT endpoint to update settings
  - [ ] Add success/error feedback via MUI Snackbar
  - Success criteria: Admins can enable/disable user creation with confirmation
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1, Story 2.3

## Affected Components

- Admin dashboard layout and navigation
- User profile management UI
- Admin user management UI
- Application branding configuration
- System settings management
- Backend APIs for all admin functions
- SystemSetting model for persisting application settings
- Confirmation dialog components for critical actions
- File upload and processing utilities

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema, Middleware)
- Material UI v6
- File upload handling (formidable)
- Image processing
- Zod for API validation

## Technical Considerations

- Admin routes require strict access control
- File uploads need proper validation and security (type, size, dimensions)
- Avatar and branding images require proper storage strategy (overwriting old files)
- User management must include safeguards (can't remove last admin)
- Settings must be properly persisted and retrieved
- Confirmation dialogs must be implemented for critical actions
- API responses should include proper error handling and validation feedback
- UI should provide clear feedback for async operations (loading, success, error)
- Admin interfaces should be responsive, though primarily focused on desktop/tablet
- SystemSetting model should have a consistent structure for different setting types
- File paths should be stored consistently and accessed efficiently

